five guineas,
desired
they might be delivered into the
hands of Rebecca.
When Harley attended our heroine at
breakfast
,
she
laid the letter on the table.
And what is this, Mrs. Harley?
said
she
, taking
it up.
A letter,
Miss
, which I was
desired
to deliver into
your hands.
From whom does it come?
A
sweet
rich gentleman, my dear young Lady,
who, having once
seen
you,
wishes
again to enjoy that
satisfaction
.
From Sir George Worthy?
Harley
courtseyed
