, but could not
speak
.
Ah! child, you may well cry,
said
Mrs.
Littleton
,
for your father is not expected to live one hour
after another.
Then lead me to him, dear mother; lead me to
him, that I may receive his
blessing
, and catch his
last
figh. Ah! he
must
not die without a parting embrace
to his Rebecca.
Mrs. Littleton made no reply, but proceeded
slowly
up the
stairs
. Rebecca followed, and in a moment
found
herself
by the bed-
side
of her
almost
