.
Oh! my father, cried Rebecca; I hope you
will recover. I hope.
Do not deceive
yourself
, my dear; my
disorder
is
a decay of nature, and a
slow
nervous fever, which the
physician
informed me
yesterday
it was
impossible
to
remove. I then
desired
your mother to
send
for you;
but tell me, my child, how is it
possible
you can have
arrived
so
soon
?
Alas! replied Rebecca, I did not know you
were ill till I arrived at the door. I came by my
Lady's
desire
to
spend
a few weeks with you and my
mother
before
she
comes into the country.
You have not offended her, Rebecca?
said
the
father.
No indeed,
said
she
, exultingly; I am higher
in her
