consider
, but
she
was well convinced to deliberate
was to be
lost
, and be had no
sooner
left her, than
she
ordered a
chaise
, and flew for protection to the arms of
her parents.
But we
soon
discovered
that the poor girl's
misfortune
would be made public. We were pitied by
some
,
laughed at and ridiculed by others, and the finger of
scorn
was pointed at my unfortunate child whenever
she
ventured abroad. We
sold
