insult
that hurt her
feelings
excessively
.
Rebecca now felt that
she
was in reality a poor
solitary
being, without a home, and
almost
without a friend;
E 2
to be
sure
Mrs. Harris had been very kind to her, but
could
she
expect that
kindness
to
last
when
she
had
lost
the power of making her any
recompense
. However
she
determined to make
some
