bosom
friend of the
best
of fathers, and though
she
seems
to have forgot that I am
her child, I can never forget
she
is my mother.
All this may be very clever, for what I know,
said
Mrs. Harris, but I am
sure
, in my opinion, it is very
ridiculous. You will find, my poor
simple
