motion with his hand.
You will be
raised
to a rank
superior
to any you
have held in the
British
army, and your name will be
immortalized as one of the glorious
supporters
of
American
liberty.
The colonel frowned
contemptuously
, and was going
to
speak
, but the
stranger
interrupted him:
You will have the felicity of
seeing
your amiable
wife and lovely daughter enjoying again the comforts
and elegancies of life.
Pleasure
will once more inhabit
their
bosoms
, and enliven their features.
The Colonel gazed tenderly on his wife and daughter,
paused
, and
seemed
