undoubted valour, he did not
blush
to indulge them.
Let
those
blush
,
said
he, mentally, who, cannot
sympathize
with an afflicted fellow creature.
But
suppose
,
said
Mrs. Abthorpe, laying her hand
on his arm, for he had mechanically
stopped
