Suppose
, Sir, you had a wife, who would
feel more for your deviation from rectitude, than
she
would to endure the
hardest
pangs of poverty and
sickness
,
and who would rather die than
see
you an
apostate
to the
cause
you had vowed for ever to
espouse
.
He turned abruptly from her;
something
that
spoke
within forbade him to
