suffering
nature wrung from her a
few complaints.Rebecca and Sophia knelt
beside
and
supported
herthe voice of comfort no longer
issued
from their lipstheir
sighs
responsive
answered
her's
their tears mingled as they fellbut all remained
silent
.
They heard
footsteps
approachthe Colonel's well
known voice
saluted
their ears.
Dry your eyes, my dear girls,
said
Mrs.
Abthorpe
;
Let us not
increase
his
sorrows
,
whose
every
pang is doubled by our
sufferings
.
The Colonel entered,
some
one accompanied him for
they could hear more than one
