before
a large fire, partaking a plentiful
supper
, while
their hearts expanded with gratitude to that good
Providence
who had
raised
them up friends when
least
expected
.
The next morning the young men exerted
themselves
to repair the breaches in the windows, and to
stop
the
large crevices in the doors of the
house
, having to the
utmost
of their power,
lessened
their troubles, and
rendered
them tolerably comfortable, they departed,
leaving
