of rejecting my
advice. She then rang the bell, and Rebecca
departed
with no very high opinion of her good nature,
whatever
her other virtues might be.
She then repaired into the city, and delivered the
other two letters, but neither of the ladies were at
home;
she
therefore immediately proceeded to her
lodgings, and informed Mrs. Harris of the
success
of
her
