of
misery
. She
stopped
, and put her hand in her pocket.
They
stood
immediately under two large lamps.
Merciful heaven! cried the poor mendicant,
laying
her cold hand on the one Rebecca had extended
with relief, and gazing ardently at herRebecca!
my child! do you not know me?
Our heroine looked intently on the pale
